Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_TERNARY_EXPRESSION post handler (10004)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_TERNARY_EXPRESSION post: lowers a ternary expression to a
conditional-select MIR pattern. The three child values (condition,
true_branch, false_branch) are already on the result stack in
visitor order. We emit a conditional-select using a compare-and-
select pattern: allocate a result temp, then emit a MIR_BRANCH
that conditionally targets two labels which each store their
respective branch value into the result, joining at a merge label.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Pop false_value (child_index 2, most recent), true_value
   (child_index 1), condition_value (child_index 0).
2. Read result_type at HIR_TERNARY_EXPRESSION offset 32.
3. Allocate true_label, false_label, merge_label and a result
   alloca slot.
4. Emit alloca for result, branch(condition, true_label,
   false_label), then for each path: label marker, store-to-alloca,
   jump-to-merge. Finally emit merge_label and a load of the
   result.
5. Push the loaded value as the ternary's result.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Five-to-seven instruction emissions per ternary. Branchless select
opcodes will replace this in a follow-up backend pass.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Missing operand values are treated as lowering errors.
@End Security_Scope

