Note: HIR_PARENTHESIZED post handler (10008)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_PARENTHESIZED post: a parenthesised expression is a pure
syntactic wrapper. The inner expression's MIR value is already on
the result stack; we leave it in place so the parent consumer sees
the same value. No MIR is emitted.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
No-op. The wrapped child's post handler already pushed the result
value onto the stack; the parent reads it the same way it would
without the wrapper.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Zero cost beyond the dispatch trampoline.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No state mutation.
@End Security_Scope

